{{defn|A point on a blow up of a variety}}

{{term|1= inflection}}
{{term|inflexion |multi=y}}
{{defn|1=  An inflection is a point where the curvature vanishes, or in other words where the tangent line meets with order at least 3. Differential geometry uses the slightly stricter condition that the curvature changes sign at the point. See {{harvtxt|Salmon|1879|loc=p. 32 }}}}

{{term|inpolar quadric}}
{{defn|See {{harv|Baker|1922|loc=volume III, p. 52, 88}}}}

