{{glossary}}

{{term|Néron–Severi group}}
{{defn|1=The [[Néron–Severi group]] is the group of divisors module numerical equivalence.}}

{{term|nest}}
{{defn|Two components (circuits) of a real algebraic curve are said to nest if one is inside the other. {{harv|Coolidge|1931}}}}

{{term|1=net}}
{{defn|no=1|1= A 2-dimensional linear system. See "pencil" and "web". See also Laguerre net.   }}
{{defn|no=2|A harmonic net is a set of points on a line containing the harmonic conjugate of any point with respect to any other two points. {{harv|Baker|1922|loc=p.133}} }}

{{term|Newton polygon}}
{{defn|{{main|Newton polygon}} The convex hull of the points with coordinates given by the exponents of the terms of a polynomial.}}

{{term|1=nodal}}
{{defn|1=A nodal tangent to a singular point of a curve is one of the lines of its [[tangent cone]]. {{harv|Semple|Roth|1949|loc=p.26}} }}

{{term|1=node}}
{{defn|1=A [[Singular point of an algebraic variety|singular point]] ''p'' of a hypersurface ''f'' = 0, usually with the determinant of the Hessian of ''f'' not zero at ''p''. {{harv|Cayley|1852}}}}

{{term|1= node cusp }}
{{defn|1=  A singularity of a curve where a node and a cusp coincide at the same point. {{harv|Salmon|1879|loc=p. 207 }}}}

{{term|1=normal}}
{{defn|no=1|defn=A subvariety of projective space is [[linearly normal]] if the linear system defining the embedding is complete; see [[rational normal curve]].}}
{{defn|no=2|defn=Orthogonal to the tangent space, such as a line orthogonal to the tangent space or the [[normal bundle]].}}
{{defn|no=3|1=A normal intersection is an intersection with the "expected" codimension (given a sum of codimensions). {{harv|Semple|Roth|loc=p.16}} }}
{{defn|no=4|defn=Local rings are integrally closed; see [[normal scheme]].}}
{{term|1=null-polarity}}
{{defn|1=A correlation given by a skew symmetric matrix. A null-polarity of the projective space of a vector space is essentially a non-degenerate skew-symmetric bilinear form, up to multiplication by scalars. See also polarity. {{harv|Semple|Roth|1949|loc=p.9}}}}

