{{defn|Short for '''Pascal line''', the line determined by 6 points of a conic in [[Pascal's theorem]]}}

{{term|1=  pedal}}
{{defn|1= The [[pedal curve]] of ''C'' with respect to a pedal point ''P'' is the locus of points ''X'' such that the line through ''X'' orthogonal to ''PX'' is tangent to ''C''. {{harv|Salmon|1879|loc=p.96  }}}}

