{{Spanish name|Baeza}} '''Ricardo Baeza Rodríguez''' is a [[Chilean people|Chilean]] [[mathematician]] who works as a professor at the [[University of Talca]].<ref name="ac"/><ref name="talca">{{citation|title=Miembro de Excelencia: Ricardo Baeza será distinguido por la American Mathematical Society|url=http://www.utalca.cl/link.cgi/SalaPrensa/academia/5382|website=Sala de Prensa|publisher=University of Talca|date=November 16, 2012|accessdate=2015-01-12}}.</ref> He earned his Ph.D. in 1970 from [[Saarland University]], under the joint supervision of Robert W. Berger and Manfred Knebusch.<ref name="talca"/><ref>{{mathgenealogy|id=58486}}.</ref> His research interest is in [[number theory]].<ref name="lanacion"/>
Baeza became a member of the Chilean Academy of Sciences in 1983.<ref name="ac">[http://www.academia-ciencias.cl/wp/?page_id=388 Member profile], Chilean Academy of Sciences, retrieved 2015-01-12.</ref> He was the 2009 winner of the Chilean [[National Prize for Exact Sciences (Chile)|National Prize for Exact Sciences]].<ref name="talca"/><ref name="lanacion">{{citation|title=Ricardo Baeza gana Premio Nacional de Ciencias Exactas|url=http://www.lanacion.cl/noticias/vida-y-estilo/ricardo-baeza-gana-premio-nacional-de-ciencias-exactas/2009-08-26/222335.html|website=Nacion.cl|date=August 27, 2009}}.</ref> In 2012, he became one of the inaugural [[fellow]]s of the [[American Mathematical Society]], the only Chilean to be so honored.<ref name="talca"/><ref>[http://www.ams.org/profession/fellows-list List of Fellows of the American Mathematical Society], retrieved 2015-01-12.</ref>
